    "The increased wind from the east and south might lead to erosion, especially during the rainy season, and could affect the topsoil fertility.",
    "Windbreaks or other protective measures may be necessary.",
    "The soil type, Acrisols, will require careful management and possibly soil amendment to maintain fertility and productivity, as they are typically acidic and low in nutrients.",
    "Lastly, Nigeria has a National Policy on Climate Change and a National Adaptation Strategy and Plan of Action on Climate Change for Nigeria.",
    "It is essential to align farming practices with these policies, which promote climate-smart agriculture and adaptation measures."
